l_id" wbmd_storage_val="1003" wbmd_disp_nm="Substance Abuse &amp; Addiction"></wbmd_c_channel_id><wbmd_c_frnd_nm>warning-to-scots-over-poor-diet-and-excessive-drinking</wbmd_c_frnd_nm><wbmd_c_asset_name></wbmd_c_asset_name><wbmd_c_teaser>As Scotland's chief medical officer warns of "unacceptable" levels of ill health, new NHS figures show adult obesity in England has reached its highest level for almost 20 years</wbmd_c_teaser><wbmd_c_mini_article object_type="wbmd_cons_shrt_txt" directive="expand" chronic_id="0000000000000000"></wbmd_c_mini_article></metadata_section><content_section><cons_news><title>Warning to Scots over poor diet and excessive drinking</title><subheadline>As Scotland's chief medical officer warns of "unacceptable" levels of ill health, new NHS figures show adult obesity in England has reached its highest level for almost 20 years</subheadline><thumbnail_image directive="imageurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8074f657" path="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/site_images/articles/thumbnails_daily_images/2011/69x75/69x75_hospital_admissions_alcohol_rise.jpg" object_type="wbmd_cons_img"></thumbnail_image><media_asset></media_asset><news_dateline>Thu, Dec 15 2011</news_dateline><pages><page><section_group><section_header></section_header><section_text><p>15th December 2011 - More work needs to be done to improve the state of health of people in Scotland, its chief medical officer has said.</p><p>Sir Harry Burns warned that <a chronic_id="091e9c5e803a6f25" crossLinkId="1585109" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e803a6f25" href="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/healthy_living/diet_and_nutrition/frequently_asked_questions_about_weight_loss" keywordId="70155" keywordSetId="31693" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/healthy_living/diet_and_nutrition/frequently_asked_questions_about_weight_loss">obesity</a>, poor <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8037b021" crossLinkId="229130" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8037b021" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Diet Center TOC_091e9c5e8037b021/page_Diet Center TOC_091e9c5e8037b021.xml" keywordId="58718" keywordSetId="25992" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Diet Center TOC_091e9c5e8037b021/page_Diet Center TOC_091e9c5e8037b021.xml">diet</a> and excessive alcohol consumption were causing "unacceptable levels of ill health".</p><p>His comments came as figures for England showed that adult obesity had reached its highest level in almost two decades.</p><p>In his sixth annual report, Sir Harry acknowledged that important strides had been made in Scotland's health, such as a decline in <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8037a71c" crossLinkId="229169" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8037a71c" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Smoking Cessation Health Center_091e9c5e8037a71c/page_Smoking Cessation Health Center_091e9c5e8037a71c.xml" keywordId="62125" keywordSetId="26017" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Smoking Cessation Health Center_091e9c5e8037a71c/page_Smoking Cessation Health Center_091e9c5e8037a71c.xml">smoking</a>-related illnesses. He also welcomed a fall in death rates from the nation's three biggest killers - <a chronic_id="091e9c5e803780a7" crossLinkId="229119" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e803780a7" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Cancer Health Center_091e9c5e803780a7/page_Cancer Health Center_091e9c5e803780a7.xml" keywordId="58720" keywordSetId="25994" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Cancer Health Center_091e9c5e803780a7/page_Cancer Health Center_091e9c5e803780a7.xml">cancer</a>, <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80378e38" crossLinkId="229137" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80378e38" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Heart Disease Health Center_091e9c5e80378e38/page_Heart Disease Health Center_091e9c5e80378e38.xml" keywordId="58704" keywordSetId="25983" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Heart Disease Health Center_091e9c5e80378e38/page_Heart Disease Health Center_091e9c5e80378e38.xml">heart disease</a> and <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8037a830" crossLinkId="229172" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8037a830" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Stroke Health Center_091e9c5e8037a830/page_Stroke Health Center_091e9c5e8037a830.xml" keywordId="58759" keywordSetId="26023" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Stroke Health Center_091e9c5e8037a830/page_Stroke Health Center_091e9c5e8037a830.xml">stroke</a>.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>Drinking and diet</section_header><section_text><p>However, he pointed to evidence that suggested Scotland had the eighth highest alcohol consumption rate in the world. He quoted figures showing that the proportion of men who reported drinking more than their recommended daily limit had risen from 43% to 45% over a seven year period.</p><p>Sir Harry also said that figures from the Scottish Health Survey revealed that between 1995 and 2010, the proportion of adults aged 16-64 who were overweight or obese increased from 52.4% to 63.3%.</p><p>On <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8047977d" crossLinkId="1627408" crossLinkType="Slideshows" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8047977d" href="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/slideshows/diet_mistakes_slideshow.xml" keywordId="58718" keywordSetId="25992" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/slideshows/diet_mistakes_slideshow.xml">diet</a>, the chief medical officer reported that only 22% of adults ate the recommended daily amount of fruit and vegetables - a figure that had not changed much in recent years. The figure was even worse for school age <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8037b75d" crossLinkId="229121" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8037b75d" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Childrens Health Page_091e9c5e8037b75d/page_Childrens Health Page_091e9c5e8037b75d.xml" keywordId="62960" keywordSetId="25991" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Childrens Health Page_091e9c5e8037b75d/page_Childrens Health Page_091e9c5e8037b75d.xml">children</a>, he said, with just 12% of five to 15 year olds eating their 5-a-day.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>Health inequalities</section_header><section_text><p>Sir Harry said that health in Scotland could be improved by a combination of legislation and helping people to help themselves. "There is willingness in Scotland to embrace new thinking in our efforts to narrow health inequalities, and make Scotland a better place to grow and develop," he wrote in the report's introduction. "If we can capitalise on this positive mind set, we can make changes which may result in significant improvements to the health and wellbeing of all Scots."</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>England health survey</section_header><section_text><p>Obesity among adults in England is at its highest level since 1993, according to new figures. <a chronic_id="091e9c5e808bc0c5" crossLinkId="1549084" crossLinkType="Article" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e808bc0c5" href="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Navigating the NHS_091e9c5e808bc0c5/page_Navigating the NHS_091e9c5e808bc0c5.xml" keywordId="70556" keywordSetId="31808" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd_uk/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD_UK/Pages/Navigating the NHS_091e9c5e808bc0c5/page_Navigating the NHS_091e9c5e808bc0c5.xml">The NHS</a> Information Centre said that 26% of men and women were overweight or obese in 2010, compared with 13% of men and 16% of women in 1993.</p><p>In total, 68% of men and 58% of women were classified as overweight or obese, according to the latest Health Survey for England.</p></section_text></section_group><section_group><section_header>Sexual behaviour</section_header><section_text><p>For the first time, the 2010 survey also examined aspects of sexual behaviour. The findings suggest that sexual behaviour has changed over the generations, with an increase in the proportion of women who say they first had sex before the age of 16.</p><p>Overall, 14% of women and 20% of men reported that they had first had sex with someone of the opposite sex before their sixteenth birthday. Among women aged between 16 and 24, this figure rose to 27%.</p><p>This contrasts with young men in the same 16 to 24 year old age band of whom 22% reported having sex when they were younger than 16 - a similar proportion to those aged 25 to 69.</p></section_text></section_group></page></pages><citations><p>SOURCES:<br>
'Health in Scotland 2010: Annual report of the chief medical officer', NHS Scotland.<br>
NHS Information Centre.</p></citations><related_links_type></related_links_type><related_links_header></related_links_header><related_links_text></related_links_text></cons_news></content_section></wbmd_asset></content><friendlyurls><target siteid="9" name="WebMD_UK_Mobile" issearchable="true" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/a-to-z-guides/news/20111215/warning-to-scots-over-poor-diet-and-excessive-drinking" owner="false"><breadcrumb><bread piece="Health News" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/a-to-z-guides/news/default.htm"></bread></breadcrumb><centers></centers></target><target siteid="7" name="WebMD_UK" issearchable="true" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/alcohol-abuse/news/20111215/warning-to-scots-over-poor-diet-and-excessive-drinking" owner="false"><breadcrumb><bread piece="Mental health centre" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/default.htm"></bread><bread piece="Alcohol abuse health centre" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/alcohol-abuse/default.htm"></bread><bread piece="Alcohol abuse news" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/alcohol-abuse/news/default.htm"></bread></breadcrumb><centers><Mini id="6367" name="" chronicid="091e9c5e8117b991" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/alcohol-abuse/default.htm" type="Mini">Alcohol Abuse</Mini><Super id="5964" name="super center" chronicid="091e9c5e8117d0a1" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/mental-health/default.htm" type="">Mental Health</Super></centers></target></friendlyurls><referenced_objects><object chronic_id="091e9c5e8037cda7" thmbnl="" pointer="0" path="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/biographies/a/ahmed_farah.wxml"><target siteid="7" name="" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/farah-ahmed"></target></object><object chronic_id="091e9c5e8043744d" thmbnl="" pointer="0" path="/webmd_uk/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/biographies/r/russell_peter.wxml"><target siteid="7" name="" prefix="www" friendlyurl="/peter-russell"></target></object><object chronic_id="091e9c5e803a6f25" thmbnl="" pointer="